INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4000","letter","1777-03-01","Middlebrook","NJ","US","George","Washington","","John","Jay","","individual","","I have taken the liberty to trouble you with this hint, as sometimes things the most obvious escape attention. If you agree with me in sentiment, you will easily fall upon the most proper mode for answering the purpose.","ltr_gwa4000.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,37,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4001","letter","1779-04-14","Middlebrook","NJ","US","George","Washington","","John","Jay","","individual","","The circumstance of which you have obliged me with a communication, is among a number of other instances of the unfriendly views which have governed a certain gentleman from a very early period.","ltr_gwa4001.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,37,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4002","letter","1779-04-00","Middlebrook","NJ","US","George","Washington","","John","Jay","","individual","","If, under this sanction, I should step beyond the line you would wish to draw, and suggest ideas or ask questions which are improper to be answered, you hare only to pass them by in silence.","ltr_gwa4002.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,37,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4003","letter","1779-05-10","Middlebrook","NJ","US","George","Washington","","John","Jay","","individual","","To me it appears that our affairs are in a very delicate situation - and what is not the least to be lamented is, that many people think they are in a very flourishing way - and seem in a great measure insensible to the danger with which we are threa","ltr_gwa4003.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,37,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4004","letter","1779-10-07","West Point","NY","US","George","Washington","","John","Jay","","individual","","Among the number of your friends, permit me also to congratulate you, and my country, on your late honourable and important appointment.","ltr_gwa4004.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,37,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4005","letter","1782-10-18","Verplancks Point","NY","US","George","Washington","","John","Jay","","individual","","We have now passed another campaign, and no very important occurrence has intervened on this side the Atlantic.","ltr_gwa4005.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,37,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4006","letter","1785-09-27","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","John","Jay","","individual","","It gave me great pleasure to hear of your appointment as secretary of the United States for the department of foreign affairs - a happier choice in my opinion could not have been made","ltr_gwa4006.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,37,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4007","letter","1788-09-03","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","John","Jay","","individual","","With peculiar pleasure I now congratulate you on the success of your labours to obtain an unconditional ratification of the proposed constitution in the Convention of your State","ltr_gwa4007.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,37,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4008","letter","1791-09-04","Philadelphia","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Jay","","individual","","The indisposition, and consequent absence from Mount Vernon, of my nephew, Major Washington, to whom the care of my private business is intrusted, makes it indispensably necessary for me to go home before the meeting of Congress.","ltr_gwa4008.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,37,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4009","letter","1794-08-30","Philadelphia","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Jay","","individual","","On this irregular and high-handed proceeding of Mr. Simcoe, which is no longer masked, I would rather hear what the ministry of Great Britain will say, than pronounce my own sentiments thereon.","ltr_gwa4009.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,37,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4010","letter","1794-11-01","Philadelphia","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Jay","","individual","","That the self-created societies which have spread themselves over this country, have been labouring incessantly to sow the seeds of distrust, jealousy, and of course discontent, thereby hoping to effect some revolution in the government, is not unkno","ltr_gwa4010.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,37,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4011","letter","1794-12-18","Philadelphia","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Jay","","individual","","As I expected, and as you have been informed the result would probably be, so it has happened, that the western insurrection has terminated highly honourable for this country","ltr_gwa4011.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,37,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4012","letter","1795-09-31","Philadelphia","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Jay","","individual","","You will have learned from the public gazettes, and through other more authentic channels, that all that rested with me to do, to give ratification to the treaty between this country and Great Britain, is already accomplished.","ltr_gwa4012.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,37,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4013","letter","1795-12-21","Philadelphia","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Jay","","individual","","My information with respect to the general disposition of the people, accords with yours - and I have little doubt of a perfect amelioration of sentiment, alter the present fermentation (which is not only subsiding, but changing) has evaporated a litt","ltr_gwa4013.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,37,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4014","letter","1796-03-31","Philadelphia","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Jay","","individual","","The purport of it is pleasing - but the conduct of the British armed vessels in the West Indies is intolerable beyond all forbearance.","ltr_gwa4014.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,37,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4450","letter","1781-04-08","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Benjamin","Tallmadge","","individual","","The success of the proposed enterprise, must depend on the absence of the British fleet, the secrecy of the attempt, and a knowledge of the exact situation of the enemy.","ltr_gwa4450.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4451","letter","1781-04-09","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","John","Laurens","","individual","","several interesting events have happened - some favorable, others adverse. Among the former may be reckoned Morgan's brilliant action with Tarleton - among the latter, the advantages gained by Lord Cornwallis over General Greene.","ltr_gwa4451.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4452","letter","1781-04-10","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Jean Baptiste","De Vimeur","","individual","","We are greatly indebted to the Chevalier Destouches for the disposition he shows to undertake the expedition to Penobscot, and to you for your readiness to furnish a detachment of troops","ltr_gwa4452.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4453","letter","1781-04-11","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Gilbert Du Motier","Lafayette","","individual","","While I give you credit for the manoeuvre by which you removed the British ships from before Annapolis, I am sorry, as matters are circumstanced, that you have put yourself so much further from the point","ltr_gwa4453.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4454","letter","1781-04-14","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Gilbert Du Motier","Lafayette","","individual","","The contingencies appeared to me so remote, in the conversations I had with Count De Rochambeau, that I could not justify myself in withdrawing a detachment already so far advanced","ltr_gwa4454.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4455","letter","1781-04-16","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Johnathan","Trumball","","individual","","Colonel Harrison, who has acted as my secretary since the beginning of 1776, has accepted an honorable and profitable civil appointment in the State of Maryland, and is gone to enjoy it.","ltr_gwa4455.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4456","letter","1781-04-18","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Nathanael","Greene","","individual","","Your private letter of the 18th ultimo came safe to hand. Although the honors of the field did not fall to your lot, I am convinced you deserved them.","ltr_gwa4456.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4457","letter","1781-04-21","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Gilbert Du Motier","Lafayette","","individual","","Though the situation of southern affairs would not permit me to recall your corps to this army, yet it was with great reluctance I could resolve upon seeing you separated from head-quarters.","ltr_gwa4457.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4458","letter","1781-04-22","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Gilbert Du Motier","Lafayette","","individual","","I have received your several letters, and am extremely concerned at the temper of your detachment, and the desertions that are taking place.","ltr_gwa4458.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4459","letter","1781-04-25","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","George","Clark","","individual","","At the request of Governor Jefferson, I have already given orders to the commandant at Fort Pitt to afford you every assistance in his power, in the prosecution of your intended expedition.","ltr_gwa4459.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4460","letter","1781-04-27","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Alexander","Hamilton","","individual","","The officers of the line contend, without having reference to particular persons, that it is a hardship and reflection upon them to introduce brevet officers into commands, of some permanence","ltr_gwa4460.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4461","letter","1781-04-30","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Jean Baptiste","De Vimeur","","individual","","I assure your Excellency, that I feel extreme pain at the occasion of that part of your letter of the 26th instant, which relates to an intercepted letter of mine published by the enemy.","ltr_gwa4461.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4462","letter","1781-04-30","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Benjamin","Tallmadge","","individual","","Besides these, you are also sensible there are many things upon a smaller scale, which are necessary to be reported, and that whatever intelligence is communicated ought to be, not in general terms, but in detail, and with the greatest precision.","ltr_gwa4462.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4463","letter","1781-04-30","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Lund","Washington","","individual","","I am very sorry to hear of your loss. I am a little sorry to hear of my own - but that which gives me most concern is, that you should go on board the enemy's vessels, and furnish them with refreshments.","ltr_gwa4463.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4464","letter","1781-05-04","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Gilbert Du Motier","Lafayette","","individual","","A false idea, arising from the consideration of his being my steward, and in that character more the trustee and guardian of my property than the representative of my honor, has misled his judgment and plunged him into error","ltr_gwa4464.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4465","letter","1781-05-05","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Gilbert Du Motier","Lafayette","","individual","","and am extremely rejoiced to learn, that the spirit of discontent had so entirely subsided, and that the parade of desertion would probably be totally stopped among the troops under your command.","ltr_gwa4465.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4466","letter","1781-05-10","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Meshech","Weare","","individual","","From the post of Saratoga to that of Dobbs's Ferry inclusive, I believe there is not (by the returns and reports I have received) at this moment one day's supply of meat for the army on hand.","ltr_gwa4466.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4467","letter","1781-05-11","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","John","Sullivan","","individual","","This, and a recent instance in the Pennsylvania regiment of artillery in proof of the absolute necessity of adopting some mode, by which the whole army may be bound, and a stop thereby be put to those disputes, which keep it in a continual state of d","ltr_gwa4467.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4468","letter","1781-05-11","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Benjamin","Lincoln","","individual","","so great are my apprehensions, on the score of provisions, that I am sending General Heath purposely to the eastern States to represent our distresses, and to endeavour to fix a plan for our regular supply in future.","ltr_gwa4468.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4469","letter","1781-05-14","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","","De Barras","","individual","","Give me leave to congratulate you on your safe arrival, and your appointment to the command of his Most Christian Majesty's fleet and sea forces upon these coasts.","ltr_gwa4469.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4471","letter","1781-05-15","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Paul","Jones","","individual","","My partial acquaintance with either our naval or commercial affairs makes it altogether impossible for me to account for the unfortunate delay of those articles of military stores and clothing","ltr_gwa4471.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4472","letter","1781-05-15","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Ezra","Styles","","individual","","For the honor conferred on me by the President and Fellows of the University of Yale College, by the degree of Doctor of Laws, my warmest thanks are offered","ltr_gwa4472.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4473","letter","1781-05-17","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Alexander","Scammell","","individual","","I have received intelligence, that a party of the enemy are establishing themselves at or near Fort Lee, and building a blockhouse, or some kind of work.","ltr_gwa4473.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4474","letter","1781-05-23","Weathersfield","NY","US","George","Washington","","Chevalier","De La Luzerne","","individual","","The letter, which I have the honor to enclose from the Count De Rochambeau, will, I imagine, inform you of the intended march of the French army towards the North River, and of the destination of the King's squadron now in the harbour of Newport","ltr_gwa4474.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4475","letter","1781-05-24","Weathersfield","NY","US","George","Washington","","Meshech","Weare","","individual","","In consequence of a conference held between the Count De Rochambeau and myself at this place, the French army will march, as soon as circumstances will admit, and form a junction with the American army upon the North River.","ltr_gwa4475.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4476","letter","1781-05-28","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Louis","Duportail","","individual","","I have only to request, therefore, that you will be pleased to make the estimates of the articles in your department necessary for the operation","ltr_gwa4476.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4477","letter","1781-05-28","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Elias","Dayton","","individual","","The late accounts from New York are mysterious and perplexing, but they at any rate demand that we should be in readiness to move.","ltr_gwa4477.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4478","letter","1781-05-29","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","John","Sullivan","","individual","","No arguments were necessary to convince me of the very great public utility, which would result from the success of the plan you proposed laying before Congress.","ltr_gwa4478.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4479","letter","1781-05-31","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Gilbert Du Motier","Lafayette","","individual","","Your conduct upon every occasion meets my approbation, but in none more than in your refusing to hold a correspondence with Arnold.","ltr_gwa4479.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4480","letter","1781-06-01","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Nathanael","Greene","","individual","","The difficulties, which you daily encounter and surmount with your small force, add not a little to your reputation","ltr_gwa4480.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4481","letter","1781-06-04","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Jean Baptiste","De Vimeur","","individual","","I had last evening the honor of receiving your favor of the 31st of May by the Duke De Lauzun, who informs me, that he is authorized by your Excellency and Count de Barras to enter into a free communication with me upon the subject of the council of","ltr_gwa4481.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4482","letter","1781-06-04","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Morris","","individual","","I felt a most sensible pleasure when I heard of your acceptance of the late appointment of Congress to regulate the finances of this country.","ltr_gwa4482.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4484","letter","1781-06-07","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","John","Mathews","","individual","","I am very sorry for the disagreeable situation of our suffering soldiery at Charleston, and wish they could be relieved without adding to the pressure under which we at present given.","ltr_gwa4484.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4485","letter","1781-06-08","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Thomas","Jefferson","","individual","","The progress, which the enemy are making in Virginia, is very alarming, not only to the State immediately invaded, but to all the rest","ltr_gwa4485.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4486","letter","1781-06-13","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Jean Baptiste","De Vimeur","","individual","","I flatter myself, that the whole convoy will arrive in safety in some of the eastern ports, as I believe the British ships are all cruising off the Hook.","ltr_gwa4486.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4487","letter","1781-06-13","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Chevalier","De La Luzerne","","individual","","Having been made acquainted by the Count De Rochambeau, with the design of the Count de Grasse to come to this coast with his fleet, I cannot forbear expressing my ardent wishes, that a body of land forces might also attend this naval armament","ltr_gwa4487.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4488","letter","1781-06-21","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","George","Clinton","","individual","","I have just received a letter from Brigadier-General Clinton, enclosing the examination of two prisoners who were taken lately by one of his scouts - from whence it appears the enemy in Canada have not made any movements in force","ltr_gwa4488.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4489","letter","1781-06-23","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","William","Irvine","","individual","","I can easily conceive the disappointment and mortification you have suffered, upon finding the flattering prospects of filling your line so unexpectedly blasted","ltr_gwa4489.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4483","letter","1781-06-05","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","James","Clinton","","individual","","The six companies of Van Schaick's regiment have since sailed. Hazen's will follow to-morrow.","ltr_gwa4483.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4490","letter","1781-06-24","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","Jean Baptiste","De Vimeur","","individual","","I have the pleasure to observe the progress you make in the march of the troops under your command, and your intentions to come to my camp in person from Hartford.","ltr_gwa4490.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4491","letter","1781-06-25","New Windsor","NY","US","George","Washington","","John","Stark","","individual","","Upon finding it necessary, for the operations of the campaign, to recall the Continental troops from the northward, I have ordered six hundred militia from the counties of Berkshire and Hampshire to that quarter","ltr_gwa4491.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4492","letter","1781-06-27","Peekskill","NY","US","George","Washington","","Jean Baptiste","De Vimeur","","individual","","It would have given me the greatest pleasure could I have made it convenient to meet you at Newtown - but independently of many arrangements, which are necessary at the first taking of the field, I am detained","ltr_gwa4492.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4493","letter","1781-06-28","Peekskill","NY","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Morris","","individual","","Your opinion of the absolute necessity of a repeal of all Under laws, before a new species of paper, though upon ever so good an establishment, will gain credit with the public, is certainly founded upon reason","ltr_gwa4493.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4494","letter","1781-06-29","Peekskill","NY","US","George","Washington","","Gilbert Du Motier","Lafayette","","individual","","I have since that heard a thousand vague reports of your situation, and that of the enemy, but none of them satisfactory.","ltr_gwa4494.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4495","letter","1781-06-30","Peekskill","NY","US","George","Washington","","David","Cobb","","individual","","Its object is to inform the Count, that I have in contemplation a very sudden surprise of some post of the enemy, which will be of very great importance in our operations","ltr_gwa4495.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4496","letter","1781-06-30","Peekskill","NY","US","George","Washington","","","Waterbury","","individual","","You will immediately on the receipt of this be pleased to collect as many men of your command as you possibly can, and march them from the place of rendezvous, so as to form a junction, without fail, with Colonel Sheldon","ltr_gwa4496.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4497","letter","1781-06-30","Peekskill","NY","US","George","Washington","","George","Clinton","","individual","","In the fullest confidence I inform you, that I intend to make an attempt by surprise upon the enemy's posts on the north end of York Island, on Monday night.","ltr_gwa4497.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4498","letter","1781-07-01","Peekskill","NY","US","George","Washington","","Benjamin","Lincoln","","individual","","My ideas, as to the most probable mode of attaining this object, have been minutely detailed in the several conversations which we have had upon the subject, and you have been furnished with such papers as I have been able to collect","ltr_gwa4498.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4499","letter","1781-07-01","Peekskill","NY","US","George","Washington","","","Waterbury","","individual","","As the Duke will be a stranger to that part of the country, which is to be the scene of your operations, it will be in your power to give him much assistance and information","ltr_gwa4499.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4500","letter","1781-07-02","Peekskill","NY","US","George","Washington","","Jean Baptiste","De Vimeur","","individual","","I think it will be very well for your Excellency to proceed to-morrow to North Castle, where you will continue until you assemble your whole force","ltr_gwa4500.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4501","letter","1781-07-02","Peekskill","NY","US","George","Washington","","Henry","Knox","","individual","","The arrangement you have made, for the periods of transportation of the heavy stores from Philadelphia, agrees perfectly with my ideas of the matter","ltr_gwa4501.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4502","letter","1781-07-03","Valentines Hill","NY","US","George","Washington","","Jean Baptiste","De Vimeur","","individual","","The operations of this day are over, and I am sorry to say, that I have not had the happiness to succeed to my wishes, although I think very essential benefit will result to our future operations from the opportunity","ltr_gwa4502.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4503","letter","1781-07-04","White Plains","NY","US","George","Washington","","Jean Baptiste","De Vimeur","","individual","","I am much inclined to wish you to give them one more day's rest in your present quarters, and the more so, as there is now no real occasion for making an uncommon degree of haste.","ltr_gwa4503.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4504","letter","1781-07-15","Dobbs Ferry","NY","US","George","Washington","","Gilbert Du Motier","Lafayette","","individual","","I sincerely congratulate you on the favorable turn of affairs announced in your last, and I hope you will be enabled to maintain that superiority, which you seem to be gaining over Lord Cornwallis.","ltr_gwa4504.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4505","letter","1781-07-13","Dobbs Ferry","NY","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Morris","","individual","","I beg you to be assured, that I never can think your correspondence tedious or troublesome. Duty as well as inclination will always prompt me to listen with pleasure to your observations upon the state of our public affairs","ltr_gwa4505.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4506","letter","1781-07-11","Dobbs Ferry","NY","US","George","Washington","","William","Alexander","","individual","","While I am with the detachment of the army below, you will remain in command here. Your principal attention will be paid to the good order of the camp, and the security of the baggage and stores left in it.","ltr_gwa4506.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4507","letter","1781-07-15","Dobbs Ferry","NY","US","George","Washington","","Richard","Lee","","individual","","The distresses of Virginia I am but too well acquainted with - but the plan you have suggested as a relief for it is, in my judgment, a greater proof of your unbounded confidence in me","ltr_gwa4507.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4508","letter","1781-07-21","Dobbs Ferry","NY","US","George","Washington","","","De Barras","","individual","","I have no doubt but the reasons which induce you to decline the removal of the squadron under your command to the Chesapeake at this time are founded in propriety","ltr_gwa4508.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4509","letter","1781-07-25","Dobbs Ferry","NY","US","George","Washington","","Samuel","Huntington","","individual","","I have been honored with your favor of the 10th, announcing your resignation of the chair of Congress and the election of Mr. McKean to that important station.","ltr_gwa4509.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4510","letter","1781-07-30","Dobbs Ferry","NY","US","George","Washington","","Nathanael","Greene","","individual","","By our movements in this quarter, and the main army taking a position near New York, and making every preparation for a serious attempt upon that place, we have already produced a happy effect","ltr_gwa4510.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4511","letter","1781-07-30","Dobbs Ferry","NY","US","George","Washington","","Gilbert Du Motier","Lafayette","","individual","","I am convinced, that your desire to be with this army arises principally from a wish to be actively useful. You will not, therefore, regret your stay in Virginia until matters are reduced to a greater degree of certainty","ltr_gwa4511.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4512","letter","1781-08-02","Dobbs Ferry","NY","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Morris","","individual","","It seems reduced almost to a certainty, that the enemy will reinforce New York with part of their troops from Virginia. In that case, the attempt against the former must be laid aside","ltr_gwa4512.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4513","letter","1781-08-02","Dobbs Ferry","NY","US","George","Washington","","Meshech","Weare","","individual","","I regret being obliged to inform your Excellency, that I find myself at this late period very little stronger than I was when the army first moved out of their quarters.","ltr_gwa4513.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4514","letter","1781-08-15","Dobbs Ferry","NY","US","George","Washington","","Gilbert Du Motier","Lafayette","","individual","","I cannot learn that any troops have yet arrived at New York from Virginia. A fleet of twenty sail came in last Saturday with troops, but they are said to be Hessian recruits from Europe.","ltr_gwa4514.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4515","letter","1781-08-16","Dobbs Ferry","NY","US","George","Washington","","Philip","Schuyler","","individual","","As the remaining part of Colonel Cortlandt's regiment is now ordered to join the main army, I have given directions to General Clinton to leave with you a small guard of men","ltr_gwa4515.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4516","letter","1781-08-17","Phillipsburg","NY","US","George","Washington","","Alexandre","De Grasse","","individual","","In consequence of the despatches received from your Excellency by the frigate Concorde, it has been judged expedient to give up for the present the enterprise against New York, and turn our attention towards the south","ltr_gwa4516.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4517","letter","1781-08-17","Dobbs Ferry","NY","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Morris","","individual","","Besides the provision necessary at the Head of Elk to carry the troops down the bay, a very considerable quantity will be wanted in Virginia.","ltr_gwa4517.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4518","letter","1781-08-19","Dobbs Ferry","NY","US","George","Washington","","William","Heath","","individual","","The security of West Point and the posts in the Highlands is to be considered the first object of your attention. In order to effect this, you will make such dispositions as in your judgement the circumstances shall from time to time require","ltr_gwa4518.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4519","letter","1781-08-21","Kings Ferry","NY","US","George","Washington","","Jean Baptiste","De Vimeur","","individual","","I am very sorry for the difficulties and impediments, which fall in the way of your march, and hope they will decrease as you proceed.","ltr_gwa4519.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4520","letter","1781-08-21","Kings Ferry","NY","US","George","Washington","","Gilbert Du Motier","Lafayette","","individual","","the troops destined for the southern quarter are now in motion. The American detachment is already on the west side of the Hudson.","ltr_gwa4520.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,38,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4550","letter","1789-10-13","New York","NY","US","George","Washington","","Gouverneur","Morris","","individual","","It being important to both countries, that the treaty of peace between Great Britain and the United States should be observed and performed with perfect and mutual good faith, and that a treaty of commerce should be concluded by them","ltr_gwa4550.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,39,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4551","letter","1789-10-13","New York","NY","US","George","Washington","","Gouverneur","Morris","","individual","","My letter to you, herewith enclosed, will give you the credence necessary to enable you to do the business, which it commits to your management, and which I am persuaded you will readily undertake.","ltr_gwa4551.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,39,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4552","letter","1789-10-13","New York","NY","US","George","Washington","","Gouverneur","Morris","","individual","","To thank you for the interesting communications contained in those letters, and for the pains you have taken to procure me a watch, is all, or nearly all, I shall attempt in this letter","ltr_gwa4552.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,39,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4553","letter","1791-07-28","Philadelphia","PA","US","George","Washington","","Gouverneur","Morris","","individual","","The change of systems, which have so long prevailed in Europe, will, undoubtedly, affect us in a degree proportioned to our political or commercial connexions with the several nations of it.","ltr_gwa4553.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,39,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4554","letter","1792-10-20","Philadelphia","PA","US","George","Washington","","Gouverneur","Morris","","individual","","gloomy indeed appears the situation of France at this juncture. But it is hardly probable that even you, who are on the spot, can say with any precision how these things will terminate","ltr_gwa4554.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,39,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4555","letter","1793-03-25","Philadelphia","PA","US","George","Washington","","Gouverneur","Morris","","individual","","And unwise should we be in the extreme, to involve ourselves in the contests of European nations, where our weight could be but small, though the loss to ourselves would be certain.","ltr_gwa4555.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,39,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4556","letter","1794-06-19","Baltimore","MD","US","George","Washington","","Gouverneur","Morris","","individual","","The difficulty, under existing circumstances, of knowing what to write to you, had determined me to write nothing","ltr_gwa4556.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,39,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4557","letter","1794-06-25","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","Gouverneur","Morris","","individual","","The sole object of the enclosed letter was to evince to you, that, notwithstanding your recall, you held the same place in my estimation that you did before it happened.","ltr_gwa4557.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,39,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa4558","letter","1790-07-07","New York","NY","US","George","Washington","","Gouverneur","Morris","","individual","","and, as far as your communications with the British Government had gone, to assure you of my entire approbation of your conduct respecting the former.","ltr_gwa4558.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,39,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa1339","letter","1789-10-13","New York","NY","US","George","Washington",NULL,"Thomas","Jefferson",NULL,"individual",NULL,"In the selection of characters to fill the important offices of Government in the United States, I was naturally led to contemplate the talents and dispositions which I knew you to possess and entertain","ltr_gwa1339.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,40,1);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa1340","letter","1789-11-30","New York","NY","US","George","Washington",NULL,"Thomas","Jefferson",NULL,"individual",NULL,"I forward your commission to Virginia - with a request to be made acquainted with your sentiments as soon as you shall find it convenient","ltr_gwa1340.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,40,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa1502","letter","1775-06-08","Philadelphia","PA","US","George","Washington",NULL,"Martha","Washington",NULL,"individual",NULL,"I am now set down to write to you on a subject which fills me with inexpressable concern...","ltr_gwa1502.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,35,1);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa1503","letter","1765-09-20","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington",NULL,"Francis","Dandridge",NULL,"individual",NULL,"If you will permit me after six years silence--the time I have been married to your Niece--to pay my respects to you in this Epistolary way...","ltr_gwa1503.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,35,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa1504","letter","1765-09-20","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington",NULL,"Robert","Cary",NULL,"individual",NULL,"As to the Stamp Act taken in a single and distinct view - one, & the first bad consequence attending of it I take to be this--our Courts of Judicature will be shut up...","ltr_gwa1504.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,35,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa1505","letter","1766-07-21","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington",NULL,"Robert","Cary",NULL,"individual",NULL,"The Repeal of the Stamp Act, to whatsoever causes owing, ought much to be rejoiced at...","ltr_gwa1505.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,35,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa1506","letter","1767-07-25","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington",NULL,"Capel","Hanbury",NULL,"individual",NULL,"Unseasonable as it may be, to take any notice of the repeal of the Stamp Act at this time, yet, I cannot help observing that a contrary measure woud have Introduced very unhappy Consequences...","ltr_gwa1506.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,35,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa1507","letter","1769-04-05","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington",NULL,"George","Mason",NULL,"individual",NULL,"At a time when our lordly Masters in Great Britain will be satisfied with nothing less than the deprivation of American freedom, it seems highly necessary that something shou'd be done...","ltr_gwa1507.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,35,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa1508","letter","1774-06-10","Williamsburg","VA","US","George","Washington",NULL,"George","Fairfax",NULL,"individual",NULL,"in short the Ministry may rely on it that Americans will never be tax'd without their own consent...","ltr_gwa1508.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,35,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa1509","letter","1774-07-04","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington",NULL,"Bryan","Fairfax",NULL,"individual",NULL,"Does it not appear, as clear as the sun in its meridian brightness, that there is a regular, systematic plan formed to fix the right and practice of taxation upon us?","ltr_gwa1509.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,35,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa1510","letter","1774-07-20","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington",NULL,"Bryan","Fairfax",NULL,"individual",NULL,"I see nothing on the one hand, to induce a belief that the Parliament would embrace a favourable oppertunity of Repealing Acts...","ltr_gwa1510.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,35,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa1511","letter","1774-08-24","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington",NULL,"Bryan","Fairfax",NULL,"individual",NULL,"For my own part, I shall not undertake to say where the Line between Great Britain and the Colonies should be drawn, but I am clearly of opinion that one ought to be drawn...","ltr_gwa1511.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,35,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa1512","letter","1774-10-09","Philadelphia","PA","US","George","Washington",NULL,"Robert","McKenzie",NULL,"individual",NULL,"George Washington letter to Robert McKenzie...","ltr_gwa1512.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,35,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa1513","letter","1775-03-25","Richmond","VA","US","George","Washington",NULL,"John","Washington",NULL,"individual",NULL,"I have promisd to review the Independant Company of Richmond sometime this Summer, they having made me a tender of the Command of it...","ltr_gwa1513.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,35,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa1514","letter","1775-05-31","Philadelphia","VA","US","George","Washington",NULL,"George","Fairfax",NULL,"individual",NULL,"Unhappy it is though to reflect, that a Brothers Sword has been sheathed in a Brothers breast, and that, the once happy and peaceful plains of America are either to be drenched with Blood, or Inha","ltr_gwa1514.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,35,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa1958","letter","1779-07-30","West Point","NY","US","George","Washington",NULL,"Anthony","Wayne",NULL,"individual",NULL,"Lord Cornwallis is undoubtedly arrived...","ltr_gwa1958.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,34,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2084","letter","1795-08-25","Philadelphia","PA","US","George","Washington",NULL,"","",NULL,"individual",NULL,"To testify to your Majesty the sincerity of the government of the United States in its negotiations, I have transmitted to John Quincy Adams...","ltr_gwa2084.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,33,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2300","letter","1778-10-28","NY","","US","George","Washington","","Aaron","Burr","","individual",NULL,"You, in my opinion, carry your ideas of delicacy too far when you propose to drop your pay while the recovery of your health necessarily requires your absence from the service.","ltr_gwa2300.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,32,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2301","letter","1779-04-03","Middlebrook","NJ","US","George","Washington","","Aaron","Burr","","individual",NULL,"Perfectly satisfied that no consideration save a desire to reestablish your health could induce you to leave the service, I cannot therefore withhold my consent.","ltr_gwa2301.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,32,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2302","letter","1779-05-19","Middlebrook","NJ","US","George","Washington","","","","","individual",NULL,"It is much to be regretted that the pleasure of obeying the first emotions in favour of misfortune is not always in our power.","ltr_gwa2302.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,32,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2600","letter","1754-03-09","Alexandria","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"In my last, by Mr. Stewart, I slightly mentioned the objection, which many had against enlisting, to wit, not knowing who was to be paymaster, or the times for payment.","ltr_gwa2600.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2601","letter","1754-03-20","","","US","George","Washington","","Richard","Corbin","","individual",NULL,"In a conversation with you at Green Spring, you gave me some room to hope for a commission above that of major, and to be ranked among the chief officers of this expedition.","ltr_gwa2601.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2602","letter","1754-03-20","Alexandria","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"I was favored with your letter by Mr. Stewart, enclosing a lieutenant-colonel's commission, and I hope my future behaviour will sufficiently testify the true sense I have of this kindness.","ltr_gwa2602.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2603","letter","1754-04-25","Wills Creek","OH","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"Mr. Ward, has this day arrived from the Fork of the Monongahela, and brings the disagreeable account, that the fort, on the 17th instant, was surrendered at the summons of Monsieur Centre cceur to a body of French","ltr_gwa2603.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2604","letter","1754-04-27","Wills Creek","OH","US","George","Washington","","James","Hamilton","","individual",NULL,"You will see, by the enclosed speech of the Half-King, that the Indians expect some assistance from you - and I am persuaded you will take proper notice of their moving speech, and their unshaken fidelity.","ltr_gwa2604.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2605","letter","1754-05-09","Little Meadows","PA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"The want of proper conveyances has much retarded this expedition, and at this time it unfortunately delays the detachment I have the honor to command.","ltr_gwa2605.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2606","letter","1754-05-18","Youghiogany","OH","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"Giving up my commission is quite contrary to my intention. Nay, I ask it as a greater favor, than any amongst the many I have received from your Honor, to confirm it to me. But let me serve voluntarily","ltr_gwa2606.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2607","letter","1754-05-18","Youghiogany","OH","US","George","Washington","","","","","individual",NULL,"These Indians contradict the report of the French having received reinforcements, though they agree that eight hundred men are very shortly expected.","ltr_gwa2607.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2608","letter","1754-05-23","","","US","George","Washington","","Joshua","Fry","","individual",NULL,"This day I returned from my discoveries down the Youghiogany, which, I am sorry to say, can never be made navigable.","ltr_gwa2608.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2609","letter","1754-05-27","Great Meadows","PA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"I received the news of your arrival at Winchester, and desire of seeing the Half-King and other chiefs of the Six Nations.","ltr_gwa2609.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2610","letter","1754-05-29","Great Meadows","PA","US","George","Washington","","Joshua","Fry","","individual",NULL,"This is by an immediate express, whom I send to inform you, that yesterday I engaged a party of French, whereof ten were killed, one wounded, and twenty-one taken, with the loss of only one of mine killed and two or three wounded","ltr_gwa2610.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2611","letter","1754-05-29","Great Meadows","PA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"I assure you, Sir, nothing is more a stranger to my breast, or a sin that my soul more abhors, than that black and detestable one of ingratitude.","ltr_gwa2611.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2612","letter","1754-05-29","Great Meadows","PA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"The bearer hereof, Monsieur Drouillon, and Monsieur La Force and two cadets, I beg leave to recommend to your particular notice, as prisoners of war, and officers whom I had the honor of taking.","ltr_gwa2612.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2613","letter","1754-05-00","Great Meadows","PA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"Since writing my last I have still stronger presumption, indeed almost confirmation, that they were sent as spies, and were ordered to wait near us, till they were truly informed of our intentions","ltr_gwa2613.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2614","letter","1754-06-10","Great Meadows","PA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"I shall with great pleasure wear the medal, which you were pleased to compliment me with, and shall present the others to Indian chiefs, as I have already done one to the Half-King.","ltr_gwa2614.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2615","letter","1754-08-11","Alexandria","VA","US","George","Washington","","William","Fairfax","","individual",NULL,"He advanced slowly as far as Gist's house, thirteen miles from the Great Meadows, employing the soldiers on the way in repairing the road, and sending out scouting parties to watch the motions of the French.","ltr_gwa2615.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2616","letter","1754-08-20","Alexandria","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"Another thing, which should be fixed indisputably, is the law we are to be guided by, whether martial or military. If the former, I must beg the favor of your Honor to give me some written orders and indemnification","ltr_gwa2616.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2617","letter","1754-00-00","","","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"I have also sent some of the soldiers' accounts, in hope of getting the money for them, as they are uneasy on that head.","ltr_gwa2617.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2618","letter","1754-11-15","","","US","George","Washington","","William","Fitzhugh","","individual",NULL,"I think the disparity between the present offer of a company and my former rank too great, to expect any real satisfaction or enjoyment in a corps, where I once had, or thought I had, a right to command","ltr_gwa2618.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2619","letter","1755-04-02","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Orme","","individual",NULL,"I find myself much embarrassed with my affairs, having no person in whom I can confide, to entrust the management of them with.","ltr_gwa2619.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2620","letter","1755-04-20","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","John","Robinson","","individual",NULL,"It is true I have been importuned to make this campaign by General Braddock, as a member of his family, he conceiving, I suppose, that the small knowledge I have had an opportunity of acquiring of the country, Indians, &c., is worthy of his notice","ltr_gwa2620.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2621","letter","1755-04-23","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","William","Fairfax","","individual",NULL,"I shall this day set out for Will's Creek, where I expect to meet the General, and to stay, I fear, too long, as the march must be regulated by the slow movements of the train - which, I am sorry to say, will be tedious","ltr_gwa2621.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2622","letter","1755-05-05","Winchester","VA","US","George","Washington","","William","Fairfax","","individual",NULL,"You will naturally conclude, that to pass through Maryland, when no object required it, was an uncommon, and an extraordinary route for the General and for Colonel Dunbar's regiment to this place.","ltr_gwa2622.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2623","letter","1755-05-14","Fort Cumberland","MD","US","George","Washington","","John","Washington","","individual",NULL,"As wearing boots is quite the mode, and mine are in a declining state, I must beg the favor of you to procure me a pair that are good and neat","ltr_gwa2623.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2624","letter","1755-06-28","Youghiogany","OH","US","George","Washington","","John","Washington","","individual",NULL,"At the Little Meadows a second council was called (for there had been one before), wherein the urgency for horses was again represented to the officers of the different corps, and how laudable a farther retrenchment of their baggage would be","ltr_gwa2624.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2625","letter","1755-06-30","Great Crossing","","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Orme","","individual",NULL,"As the Doctor thinks it imprudent for me to use much exercise for two or three days, my movements will be retarded.","ltr_gwa2625.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2626","letter","1755-07-15","Little Meadows","PA","US","George","Washington","","","Innes","","individual",NULL,"The horses, which carry the wounded gentlemen in litters, are so much fatigued, that we dread their performance - therefore, it is desired that you will be kind enough to send out eight or ten fresh horses","ltr_gwa2626.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2627","letter","1755-07-18","Fort Cumberland","MD","US","George","Washington","","Mary","Washington","","individual",NULL,"As I doubt not but you have heard of our defeat, and, perhaps, had it represented in a worse light, if possible, than it deserves, I have taken this earliest opportunity to give you some account of the engagement as it happened","ltr_gwa2627.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2628","letter","1755-07-18","Fort Cumberland","MD","US","George","Washington","","John","Washington","","individual",NULL,"We have been most scandalously beaten by a trifling body of men, but fatigue and want of time prevent me from giving you any of the details, until I have the happiness of seeing you at Mount Vernon","ltr_gwa2628.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2629","letter","1755-08-02","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Jackson","","individual",NULL,"I must own, I was not a little surprised to find, that Governor Innes was the means of alarming the country with a report so extraordinary, without having better confirmation of the truth, than the story of an affrighted wagoner!","ltr_gwa2629.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2630","letter","1755-08-02","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","Augustine","Washington","","individual",NULL,"so little am I dispirited at what has happened, I am always ready, and always willing, to render my country any services that I am capable of, but never upon the terms I have done","ltr_gwa2630.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2631","letter","1755-08-14","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","Mary","Washington","","individual",NULL,"If it is in my power to avoid going to the Ohio again, I shall - but if the command is pressed upon me, by the general voice of the country, and offered upon such terms as cannot be objected against, it would reflect dishonor upon me to refuse it","ltr_gwa2631.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2632","letter","1755-08-14","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","Warner","Lewis","","individual",NULL,"The chief cause, next to indisposition, that prevented me from going down to this Assembly, was a determination not to offer my services - and that determination proceeded from the following reasons.","ltr_gwa2632.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2633","letter","1755-09-06","Fredericksburg","VA","US","George","Washington","","Andrew","Lewis","","individual",NULL,"The country has come to a resolution to raise sixteen companies, which are to be formed into a regiment, and of which they have honored me with the command.","ltr_gwa2633.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2634","letter","1755-09-11","Alexandria","VA","US","George","Washington","","John","Robinson","","individual",NULL,"After a small halt at Fredericksburg, to issue orders to the recruiting officers appointed to that rendezvous, I proceeded to this place, in order to collect a return of the provisions and clothing","ltr_gwa2634.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2635","letter","1755-10-08","Fredericksburg","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"I shall set out this evening for Winchester, where I expect to be joined by the recruits from Alexandria and this place, as soon as they can possibly march that distance","ltr_gwa2635.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2636","letter","1755-10-11","Winchester","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"I was told by Colonel Martin, who had attempted to raise the militia for the same purpose, that it was impossible to get above twenty or twenty-five men, they having absolutely refused to stir","ltr_gwa2636.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2637","letter","1755-10-17","Winchester","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"In however trifling a light the attempts of the French to alienate the affections of our southern Indians may at first appear, I must look upon it as a thing of the utmost consequence, requiring our greatest and most immediate attention.","ltr_gwa2637.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2638","letter","1755-11-28","Alexandria","VA","US","George","Washington","","Adam","Stephen","","individual",NULL,"There has been such total negligence among the recruiting officers in general, such disregard of the service they were employed in, and such idle proceedings, that I am determined to send out none until we all meet","ltr_gwa2638.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2639","letter","1755-12-28","Winchester","VA","US","George","Washington","","Adam","Stephen","","individual",NULL,"see that the troops are duly drawn out and trained to their exercise, and practised to bush-fighting.","ltr_gwa2639.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2640","letter","1756-01-05","Winchester","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Morris","","individual",NULL,"There is nothing more necessary than good intelligence to frustrate a designing enemy, and nothing that requires greater pains to obtain.","ltr_gwa2640.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2641","letter","1756-01-14","Alexandria","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"I have given all necessary orders for- training the men to a proper use of their arms, and the method of Indian fighting, and hope in a little time to make them expert.","ltr_gwa2641.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2642","letter","1756-01-14","Alexandria","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"When I was down, the Committee among other things resolved, that the Maryland and Carolina companies should not be supported with our provisions.","ltr_gwa2642.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2643","letter","1756-02-01","Alexandria","VA","US","George","Washington","","Adam","Stephen","","individual",NULL,"You may tell Mr. Livingston from me, that, if the soldiers are not skilled in arms equal to what may reasonably be expected, he most assuredly shall answer for it at my return.","ltr_gwa2643.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2644","letter","1756-02-02","Alexandria","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"I can but return my very hearty thanks for your kind condescension in suffering me to wait upon General Shirley, as I am very well assured it was done with the intention to favor my suit.","ltr_gwa2644.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2645","letter","1756-04-07","Winchester","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"The enemy have returned in greater numbers, committed several murders not far from Winchester, and even are so daring as to attack our forts in open day","ltr_gwa2645.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2646","letter","1756-04-18","Winchester","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"I wrote your Honor in my last how unsuccessfully we attempted to raise the militia, and that I was reduced to the necessity of waiting here for the arrival of an escort from Fort Cumberland.","ltr_gwa2646.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2647","letter","1756-04-19","Winchester","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"I immediately consulted Governor Innes, and such officers of my regiment as were at this place, on the necessary steps to be taken. They unanimously advised, that I should remain here with the fifty recruits that are in town","ltr_gwa2647.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2648","letter","1756-04-22","Winchester","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"This encloses several letters, and the minutes of a council of war, which was held upon the receipt of them. Your Honor may see to what unhappy straits the distressed inhabitants and myself are reduced.","ltr_gwa2648.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2649","letter","1756-04-24","Winchester","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"Three families were murdered the night before last, at the distance of less than twelve miles from this place - and every day we have accounts of such cruelties and barbarities, as are shocking to human nature.","ltr_gwa2649.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2650","letter","1756-04-24","Winchester","VA","US","George","Washington","","John","Robinson","","individual",NULL,"You may expect, by the time this comes to hand, that, without a considerable reinforcement, Frederic county will not be mistress of fifteen families. They are now retreating to the securest parts in droves of fifties.","ltr_gwa2650.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2651","letter","1756-04-27","Winchester","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"The inhabitants, who are now in forts, are greatly distressed for the want of ammunition and provision, and are incessantly importuning me for both - neither of which have I at this place to spare.","ltr_gwa2651.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2652","letter","1756-05-03","Winchester","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"I have sent down an Indian scalp, which was taken at the place where Captain Mercer had his engagement. He was found thrust under some rocks, with stones piled up against them.","ltr_gwa2652.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2653","letter","1756-06-25","Winchester","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"Your Honor never gave me a decisive answer to a question I asked, about assigning companies to the fieldofficers. For this reason I have presumed to repeat it again","ltr_gwa2653.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2654","letter","1756-08-04","Winchester","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"Giving the necessary orders and directions, about the chain of forts to be built on the frontiers, has kept me so closely employed, that I could not write fully to you until this time.","ltr_gwa2654.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2655","letter","1756-08-05","Winchester","VA","US","George","Washington","","John","Robinson","","individual",NULL,"Fort Cumberland at present contains all our provisions and valuable stores, and is not capable of an hour's defence, if the enemy were only to bring a single halfpounder against it - which they might do with great ease on horseback.","ltr_gwa2655.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2656","letter","1756-08-14","Winchester","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"Repeated complaints and applications from all quarters for men, but more especially from the garrisons, which secure the communication with Fort Cumberland, obliged me to order a company from Captain Waggeners detachment","ltr_gwa2656.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2657","letter","1756-08-29","Winchester","VA","US","George","Washington","","","Fairfax","","individual",NULL,"It is with infinite concern, that I see the distresses o the people, and hear their complaints, without being able to afford them relief. I have so often troubled you for aid from the militia, that I am almost ashamed to repeat my demands","ltr_gwa2657.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2658","letter","1756-09-23","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"Under your kind indulgence I came to this place a few days ago, expecting to meet the executors of my deceased brother, in order to make a final settlement of his affairs.","ltr_gwa2658.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2659","letter","1756-10-10","Halifax","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"Finding that it was impossible to get a party to range and scour the frontiers, it remained only to proceed without men to see the situation of the forts, or to return back.","ltr_gwa2659.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2660","letter","1756-11-09","Winchester","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"With this small company of irregulars, with whom order, regularity, circumspection, and vigilance were matters of derision and contempt, we set out, and, by the protection of Providence, reached Augusta Court-House in seven days","ltr_gwa2660.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2661","letter","1756-12-02","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"if you were truly informed of the situation of this place, of its importance and danger, you would not think it prudent to leave such a quantity of valuable stores exposed to the insults of a few","ltr_gwa2661.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2662","letter","1756-12-17","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","William","Bronaugh","","individual",NULL,"You are strictly required, immediately upon receipt of this, to transmit your provisions and stores to Captain Waggener's Fort, and there leave them.","ltr_gwa2662.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2663","letter","1756-12-19","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"I am a little at a loss to understand the meaning of your orders, and the opinion of the Council, when I am directed to evacuate all the stockade forts, and at the same time to march only one hundred men to Fort Cumberland","ltr_gwa2663.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2664","letter","1756-12-19","Winchester","VA","US","George","Washington","","John","Robinson","","individual",NULL,"We are ordered to reinforce Fort Cumberland with one hundred men, and, to enable me to carry that number thither, all the stockade forts on the Branch are to be evacuated, and in course all the settlements abandoned","ltr_gwa2664.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2665","letter","1757-02-00","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Campbell","","individual",NULL,"The posture of affairs in this quarter is really melancholy, and the prospect was rendered more gloomy while there appeared no hopes of amendment - but, from the presence of your Lordship at this time in the Dominion, we conceive hopes of seeing these","ltr_gwa2665.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2666","letter","1757-04-15","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","Richard","Washington","","individual",NULL,"I have been posted, then, for twenty months past upon our cold and barren frontiers, to perform, I think I may say, impossibilities - that is, to protect from the cruel incursions of a crafty, savage enemy a line of inhabitants, of more than three hu","ltr_gwa2666.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2667","letter","1757-04-16","Fort Cumberland","MD","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"Your letter by express, of the 5th instant, I fear has fallen into the hands of the common enemy, for I never have seen it.","ltr_gwa2667.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2668","letter","1757-05-30","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Robinson","","individual",NULL,"We receive fresh proofs every day of the bad direction of our Indian affairs. It is not easy to tell what expenses have arisen on account of these Indians, how dissatisfied they are, and how gloomy the prospect of pleasing them appears","ltr_gwa2668.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2669","letter","1757-06-10","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Robinson","","individual",NULL,"A person of a readier pen, and having more time, than myself, might amuse you with the vicissitudes, which have happened in the Indian affairs since Mr. Atkin came up.","ltr_gwa2669.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2670","letter","1757-06-15","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Stanwix","","individual",NULL,"A scouting party, consisting of five soldiers and fifteen Cherokee Indians, who were sent out the 20th ultimo towards the Ohio, under Lieutenant Baker, returned the 8th instant to Fort Cumberland with five scalps, and a French officer","ltr_gwa2670.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2671","letter","1757-06-16","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"If the enemy are coming down in such numbers, and with such a train of artillery, as we are bid to expect, Fort Cumberland must inevitably fall into their hands, as no timely efforts can be made to relieve the garrison.","ltr_gwa2671.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2672","letter","1757-06-20","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Stanwix","","individual",NULL,"It is altogether evident, if the Indian accounts may be relied on, that the French are bringing howitzers with them for the easier reduction of the place, if they should attack us.","ltr_gwa2672.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2673","letter","1757-06-28","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Stanwix","","individual",NULL,"but since you are so kind as to leave it discretionary with me, I freely confess, that I cannot entertain any thoughts of parting with the fewsoldiers I have, to strengthen a place that now seems to be in no actual danger.","ltr_gwa2673.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2674","letter","1757-07-30","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Stanwix","","individual",NULL,"My former letters would inform you how little share I had in confining the Indians to the public jail at this place.","ltr_gwa2674.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2675","letter","1757-08-27","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"The drafts from Lunenburg are arrived, to the num ber of sixteen, which does not replace the soldiers, that have deserted since my last.","ltr_gwa2675.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2676","letter","1757-09-17","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"I apprehend, that thirteen of the twenty -nine drafts from Lunenburg have deserted, as sixteen only have arrived here, and I have no accounts of any more being on their march.","ltr_gwa2676.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2677","letter","1757-09-17","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"It is evident, from a variety of circumstances, and especially from the change in your Honor's conduct towards me, that some person, as well inclined to detract, but better skilled in the art of detraction, than the author of the above stupid scandal","ltr_gwa2677.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2678","letter","1757-09-18","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","William","Peachey","","individual",NULL,"it will be needless, I dare say, to observe further at this time, than that the liberty, which he has been pleased to allow himself in sporting with my character, is little else than a comic entertainment","ltr_gwa2678.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2679","letter","1757-09-24","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"The inhabitants of this valuable and very fertile valley are terrified beyond expression. Some have abandoned their plantations, and many are packing up their most valuable effects to follow them.","ltr_gwa2679.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2680","letter","1757-10-05","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"As I cannot now send a proper monthly return of the regiment, for want of the remarks of the officers at the out-posts","ltr_gwa2680.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2681","letter","1757-10-08","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Stanwix","","individual",NULL,"I am favored with an opportunity ... to inform you of a very extraordinary affair, which has happened at this place, namely, the desertion of our quartermaster.","ltr_gwa2681.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2682","letter","1757-10-25","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Robinson","","individual",NULL,"I applied to the Governor for permission to go down and settle my accounts before he leaves the country, and to represent the melancholy situation of our distressed frontiers, which no written narrative can so well describe, as a verbal account","ltr_gwa2682.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2683","letter","1757-11-05","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Dinwiddie","","individual",NULL,"I again trouble your Honor on the subject of Indian affairs here, which have been impeded and embarrassed by such a train of mismanagement, as, if continued, must produce melancholy consequences.","ltr_gwa2683.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2684","letter","1758-01-30","Fredericksburg","VA","US","George","Washington","","John","Blair","","individual",NULL,"Hearing of the Governor's departure for England, I think it a duty incumbent on me to inform your Honor, that I lingered a long time under an illness, which obliged me to retire from my command, by the surgeon's advice","ltr_gwa2684.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2685","letter","1758-02-20","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","John","Blair","","individual",NULL,"I set out for Williamsburg the day after the date of my letter, but found I was unable to proceed, my fever and pain increasing upon me to a high degree","ltr_gwa2685.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2686","letter","1758-03-04","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","John","Stanwix","","individual",NULL,"Pray, does not his plan sufficiently indicate the man? Can there be a better index to his abilities, than his scheme for reducing the enemy on the Ohio, and his expeditious march of a thousand men to Detroit?","ltr_gwa2686.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2687","letter","1758-04-10","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Stanwix","","individual",NULL,"Permit me, at the same time that I congratulate you, which I most sincerely do, on your promotion, so justly merited, to express my concern at the prospect of parting with you.","ltr_gwa2687.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2688","letter","1758-04-12","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","Francis","Halket","","individual",NULL,"Are we to have you once more among us? And shall we revisit together a hapless spot, that proved so fatal to many of our former brave companions?","ltr_gwa2688.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2689","letter","1758-04-17","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Blair","","individual",NULL,"I think it incumbent on me to be informed by your Honor, how the regiment under my command is to be furnished with tents, ammunition, cartridge-paper, and many other requisites, that may be wanted in the course of the campaign.","ltr_gwa2689.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2690","letter","1758-04-23","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Forbes","","individual",NULL,"I have no higher ambition, than to act my part well during the campaign - and if I should thereby merit your approbation, it will be a most pleasing reward for the toils I shall undergo.","ltr_gwa2690.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2691","letter","1758-04-24","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Blair","","individual",NULL,"I could by no means think of executing, willingly, that discretionary power, with which you were pleased to invest me, of ordering out the militia, It is an affair, Sir, of too important and delicate a nature for me to manage.","ltr_gwa2691.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2692","letter","1758-04-27","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","St. Clair","","individual",NULL,"I have received Mr. President's orders to obey any command you shall be pleased to honor me with - also to tell you, that the two companies from Carolina were at Fredericksburg, and may be expected here daily.","ltr_gwa2692.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2693","letter","1758-05-11","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","Francis","Halket","","individual",NULL,"I must, therefore, beg that you will, from me, assure the General, that the Catawbas have not this year brought in one prisoner or scalp to this place, nor indeed to any other that I have heard of.","ltr_gwa2693.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2694","letter","1758-05-28","Williamsburg","VA","US","George","Washington","","John","Blair","","individual",NULL,"I came here at this critical juncture, by the express order of Sir John St. Clair, to represent in the fullest manner the posture of our affairs at Winchester, and to obviate any doubts, that might arise from the best written narrative.","ltr_gwa2694.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2695","letter","1758-06-17","Fort Loudoun","PA","US","George","Washington","","Francis","Fauquier","","individual",NULL,"Although but little skilled in compliments, permit me nevertheless to offer your Honor my congratulations on your appointment, and your safe arrival at a government","ltr_gwa2695.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2696","letter","1758-07-03","Fort Cumberland","MD","US","George","Washington","","Henry","Bouquet","","individual",NULL,"According to orders I marched from Winchester on the 24th ultimo, and arrived at this place yesterday, with five companies of the first Virginia regiment, and a company of artificers from the second","ltr_gwa2696.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2697","letter","1758-07-09","Fort Cumberland","MD","US","George","Washington","","Henry","Bouquet","","individual",NULL,"Colonel Byrd, with eight companies of his regiment, arrived here yesterday. He left many sick men behind, and, as he posted a company at Edwards's and Pearsall's, our strength is considerably reduced.","ltr_gwa2697.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2698","letter","1758-07-16","Fort Cumberland","MD","US","George","Washington","","Henry","Bouquet","","individual",NULL,"I was favored with your letter of the 14th instant, at eleven o'clock last night. The express, who brought it, informs me, that he was twice fired upon by Indians, and was obliged to abandon his horse to save himself.","ltr_gwa2698.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2699","letter","1758-07-19","Fort Cumberland","MD","US","George","Washington","","Henry","Bouquet","","individual",NULL,"I am exceedingly obliged by the handsome and polite manner, in which you are pleased to give me leave to attend the election at Winchester.","ltr_gwa2699.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2710","letter","1758-11-17","Bushy Run","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Forbes","","individual",NULL,"After the most constant labor from daybreak till night, we were able to open the road only as far as this place, about six miles from our last camp.","ltr_gwa2710.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2711","letter","1758-11-18","Armstong's Camp","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Forbes","","individual",NULL,"I thought it expedient to halt here till three in the morning, when I shall begin to march with one thousand men, leaving Colonel Armstrong and five hundred more in this camp","ltr_gwa2711.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2712","letter","1758-11-28","Fort Duquesne","PA","US","George","Washington","","Francis","Fauquier","","individual",NULL,"I have the pleasure to inform you, that Fort Duquesne, or the ground rather on which it stood, was possessed by his Majesty's troops on the 25th instant. The enemy, after letting us get within a day's march of the place, burned the fort, and ran away","ltr_gwa2712.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2713","letter","1758-12-02","Loyal Hanna","PA","US","George","Washington","","Francis","Fauquier","","individual",NULL,"The General has, in his letters, told you what garrison he proposed to leave at Fort Duquesne, but the want of provisions rendered it impossible to leave more than two hundred men in all","ltr_gwa2713.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2714","letter","1758-12-09","Winchester","VA","US","George","Washington","","Francis","Fauquier","","individual",NULL,"Reason, nay, common humanity itself points out, that some respite should be granted to troops returning from every toil and hardship, that cold, hunger, and fatigue can inflict, and I hope your sentiments correspond wit mine.","ltr_gwa2714.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2715","letter","1758-12-30","Williamsburg","VA","US","George","Washington","","John","Forbes","","individual",NULL,"Captain M c Neil, who commanded the first Virginia regiment in my absence, committed an error, I am informed, at Raystown, in confining Mr. Hoops, the commissary.","ltr_gwa2715.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2716","letter","1759-05-01","Williamsburg","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Cary","","individual",NULL,"I shall continue to make you the same consignments of tobacco as usual, and will endeavour to increase them in proportion as I find myself and the estate benefited thereby.","ltr_gwa2716.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2717","letter","1759-06-12","","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Cary","","individual",NULL,"In my last, among other things, I desired you would send me, besides a small octavo volume, the best system now extant of agriculture.","ltr_gwa2717.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2718","letter","1759-09-20","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Cary","","individual",NULL,"I am now, I believe, fixed at this seat with an agreeable partner for life, and I hope to find more happiness in retirement, than I ever experienced amidst the wide and bustling world.","ltr_gwa2718.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2719","letter","1760-08-10","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","Richard","Washington","","individual",NULL,"The French are so well drubbed, and seem so much humbled in America, that I apprehend our generals will find it no difficult matter to reduce Canada to our obedience this summer.","ltr_gwa2719.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2724","letter","1763-05-02","Williamsburg","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Stewart","","individual",NULL,"Signing the definitive treaty seems to be the only piece of news, which prevails here at present, and diffuses general joy.","ltr_gwa2724.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2723","letter","1761-11-03","Williamsburg","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Cary","","individual",NULL,"Our Assembly is at present convened to grant supplies for carrying on the war against the Cherokee Indians, should they choose to continue it","ltr_gwa2723.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2722","letter","1761-10-20","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","Richard","Washington","","individual",NULL,"I have in appearance been very near my last breath. My indisposition increased upon me, and I fell into a very low and dangerous state. I once thought the grim king would certainly master my utmost efforts","ltr_gwa2722.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2721","letter","1761-07-14","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","Richard","Washington","","individual",NULL,"The entire conquest of Canada, and of the French in most parts of North America, being a story too stale to relate in these days, we are often at a loss for something with which to fill our letters.","ltr_gwa2721.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2720","letter","1760-11-20","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Mackenzie","","individual",NULL,"For, Sir, with not more pleasure than truth, I can declare to you and the world, that while I had the honor of commanding the regiment, your conduct, both as an officer and a gentleman, was unexceptionable","ltr_gwa2720.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2700","letter","1758-07-21","Fort Cumberland","MD","US","George","Washington","","Henry","Bouquet","","individual",NULL,"I had, before Colonel Stephen came to this place, abandoned all thoughts of attending personally the election at Winchester, choosing rather to leave the management of that affair to my friends","ltr_gwa2700.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2701","letter","1758-07-25","Fort Cumberland","MD","US","George","Washington","","Henry","Bouquet","","individual",NULL,"would it not facilitate the operation of the campaign, if the Virginia troops were ordered to proceed as far as the Great Crossing, and construct forts at the most advantageous situations as they advance","ltr_gwa2701.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2702","letter","1758-08-02","Fort Cumberland","MD","US","George","Washington","","Francis","Halket","","individual",NULL,"I am just returned from a conference with Colonel Bouquet. I find him fixed, I think I may say unalterably fixed, to lead you a new way to the Ohio, through a road, every inch of which is to be cut at this advanced season","ltr_gwa2702.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2703","letter","1758-08-02","Fort Cumberland","MD","US","George","Washington","","Henry","Bouquet","","individual",NULL,"The matters, of which we spoke relative to the roads, have, since our parting, been the subject of my closest reflection - and, so far am I from altering my opinion, that, the more time and attention I bestow, the more I am confirmed in it","ltr_gwa2703.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2704","letter","1758-08-18","Fort Cumberland","MD","US","George","Washington","","Henry","Bouquet","","individual",NULL,"I am favored with yours of yesterday, intimating a probability of my proceeding with a body of troops, on General Braddock's road, and desiring me to retain for that purpose a month's provisions at this place","ltr_gwa2704.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2705","letter","1758-08-21","Fort Cumberland","MD","US","George","Washington","","","","","individual",NULL,"Twenty-five Catawbas came here this evening, and the convoy may be expected the day after to-morrow, as it was at PearsalPs last night.","ltr_gwa2705.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2706","letter","1758-09-01","Fort Cumberland","MD","US","George","Washington","","John","Robinson","","individual",NULL,"That appearance of glory, which we had once in view, that hope, that laudable ambition of serving our country, and meriting its applause, are now no more - all is dwindled into ease, sloth, and fatal inactivity.","ltr_gwa2706.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2707","letter","1758-10-08","Raystown","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Forbes","","individual",NULL,"I offer these plans to your consideration. They express my thoughts respecting a line of march through a country covered with woods, and how that line of march may be formed quickly","ltr_gwa2707.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2708","letter","1758-10-30","Loyal Hanna","PA","US","George","Washington","","Francis","Fauquier","","individual",NULL,"I am sorry to inform you, that, upon reviewing the six companies of my regiment at this place, which had been separated from me since my last, I found them deficient in the necessaries contained in the enclosed return.","ltr_gwa2708.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2709","letter","1758-11-15","Chestnut Ridge","PA","US","George","Washington","","John","Forbes","","individual",NULL,"An express from Colonel Armstrong affords me an opportunity of informing you, that we arrived here about four o'clock this afternoon.","ltr_gwa2709.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2725","letter","1763-08-13","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Stewart","","individual",NULL,"Another tempest has arisen upon our frontiers, and the alarm spread wider than ever. In short, the inhabitants are so apprehensive of danger, that no families remain above the Conococheague road, and many are gone below it.","ltr_gwa2725.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2726","letter","1764-02-13","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","Robert","Cary","","individual",NULL,"We have been curiously entertained, of late, with the description of an engine lately constructed, I believe, in Switzerland, and which has undergone some improvements in England, for taking up trees by the roots.","ltr_gwa2726.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2729","letter","1767-09-21","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","William","Crawford","","individual",NULL,"I then desired the favor of you ... to look me out a tract of about fifteen hundred, two thousand, or more acres somewhere in your neighbourhood","ltr_gwa2729.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2730","letter","1769-01-29","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","William","Ramsay","","individual",NULL,"I should be glad, if you have no other objection to it than the expense, if you would send him to that college, as soon as convenient, and depend on me for twentyfive pounds a year for his support","ltr_gwa2730.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2732","letter","1770-04-15","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","","Botetourte","","individual",NULL,"By the extracts, which your Excellency did me the honor to enclose, I perceive, that the petitioners propose to begin opposite to the mouth of the Scioto River","ltr_gwa2732.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2733","letter","1771-06-15","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","John","Murray","","individual",NULL,"The very obliging offer your Lordship was pleased to make, the day I left Williamsburg, in behalf of the officers and soldiers, who, under the faith of government, lay claim to two hundred thousand acres of land","ltr_gwa2733.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2734","letter","1771-07-09","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","Johnathan","Boucher","","individual",NULL,"In my last I informed you, that the friends (I do not by this confine myself to the relations only) of Mr. Custis were divided in opinion, as to the propriety of his travelling","ltr_gwa2734.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2735","letter","1771-11-07","Williamsburg","VA","US","George","Washington","","George","Mercer","","individual",NULL,"Since you first left this country, I have been favored with two letters from you - one of them serving to enter your own, and the claims of Captains Stobo and Vanbraam, to part of the two hundred thousand acres of land","ltr_gwa2735.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2736","letter","1773-03-25","","VA","US","George","Washington","","William","Edwards","","individual",NULL,"Mr. Wood, the bearer of this, is a gentleman of Virginia, going upon a tour to Florida. He proposes, before his return, to explore some of the ungranted lands in your government","ltr_gwa2736.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2737","letter","1773-04-03","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","Benedict","Calvert","","individual",NULL,"My son-in-law and ward, Mr. Custis, has, as I have been informed, paid his addresses to your second daughter, and, having made some progress in her affections, has solicited her in marriage.","ltr_gwa2737.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2738","letter","1773-04-13","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","John","Murray","","individual",NULL,"I beg the favor of your Lordship to inform me, therefore, as nearly as you can, of the precise time you will do me the honor of calling here, that I may get ready accordingly, and give notice of it to Mr. Crawford","ltr_gwa2738.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2739","letter","1773-05-31","New York","NY","US","George","Washington","","","Cooper","","individual",NULL,"Enclosed you have a set of bills for one hundred pounds sterling, which please to set at the prevailing exchange, and retain the money in your own hands to answer Mr. Custis's expenses at college","ltr_gwa2739.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2740","letter","1773-09-25","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","William","Crawford","","individual",NULL,"I have heard, .... that his Lordship will grant patents for lands lying below the Scioto, to the officers and soldiers, who claim under the proclamation of October, 1763.","ltr_gwa2740.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2741","letter","1773-11-02","Williamsburg","VA","US","George","Washington","","John","Murray","","individual",NULL,"I take the liberty of addressing your Excellency on the subject of the lands, which the gentlemen conceive themselves entitled to under his Majesty's bounty of October, 1763.","ltr_gwa2741.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2742","letter","1773-12-13","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","","Cooper","","individual",NULL,"The favorable account, which you were pleased to transmit to me, of Mr. Custis's conduct at college, gave me very great satisfaction. I hoped to have felt an increase of it by his continuance at that place","ltr_gwa2742.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2743","letter","1774-02-00","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","James","Tilghman","","individual",NULL,"Interested as well as political motives render it necessary for me to seat the lands, which I have patented on the Ohio, in the cheapest, most expeditious, and effectual manner.","ltr_gwa2743.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2744","letter","1774-02-22","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","Henry","Riddell","","individual",NULL,"Mr. Young, hearing me express a desire of importing Palatines to settle on my lands on the Ohio, tells me, that, in discoursing of this matter in your company, you suggested an expedient, which might probably be attended with success","ltr_gwa2744.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2745","letter","1774-06-16","Williamsburg","VA","US","George","Washington","","Edward","Snickers","","individual",NULL,"Enclosed you will receive Mr. Hughes's warrant in his own right, for two thousand acres of land, the getting of which, at this time, he must look upon as a very great favor, as the Governor has dispensed with two positive instructions to oblige him.","ltr_gwa2745.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2750","letter","1775-01-13","Mount Vernon","VA","US","George","Washington","","John","West","","individual",NULL,"two things are essentially necessary in the man to whom this charge is committed, a capacity of judging with propriety of measures proper to be taken in the government of a youth, and leisure sufficient to attend to the execution of these measures.","ltr_gwa2750.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2751","letter","1775-03-25","Richmond","VA","US","George","Washington","","John","Washington","","individual",NULL,"I had like to have forgotten to express my entire approbation of the laudable pursuit you are engaged in, of training an independent company.","ltr_gwa2751.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ("ltr_gwa2752","letter","1775-05-31","Philadelphia","PA","US","George","Washington","","William","Fairfax","","individual",NULL,"Before this letter will come to hand, you must undoubtedly have received an account of the engagement in the Massachusetts Bay, between the ministerial troops... and the provincials of that government.","ltr_gwa2752.txt","hans.brough@yahoo.com",NULL,20090802183836,NULL,36,0);
